{
  "texts": [
    "More details about the technical implementation are provided in Appendix A.One of the most crucial design choices is the selection of a contrastive dataset representative of the preference dimension.",
    "The dataset should contain gold standard exemplars of what the ideal positive and negative LLM responses look like -for example, to probe for truthfulness, Li et al.",
    "contrasts factual responses with incorrect responses.",
    "However, as the preference dimensions in our task domain lack high quality data, especially samples that follow the format of helpful LLM responses, we artificially constructed the datasets by prompting a state-of-art LLM (GPT-4o) to output responses that would satisfy users of both the positive and negative axes of the preference dimension.",
    "This attained better quality than alternative datasets, such as a list of synonymous adjectives and the Yelp reviews."
  ]
}